Sounds of the Jungle¶

Extracting sounds of individual animals from an audio recording of the jungle by applying Fast Fourier Transform (FFT), filtering and analysing spectrograms.

In [4]:
# spectrum
signal_ = data
signalFFT = fftshift(fft(signal_))

freqs = np.arange(signal_.size)

# zero frequency is in the centre
freqs = freqs - (signal_.size)//2

# Obtain frequency in Hz
freqsSecs = freqs/(signal_.size/sample_rate)

sns.lineplot(x = freqsSecs, y = np.abs(signalFFT))
plt.ylabel('Coefficients')
plt.xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
sns.despine()
In [5]:
# spectrogram
f, t, Sxx = signal.spectrogram(signal_, sample_rate)

plt.pcolormesh(t, f, np.log(Sxx))
plt.xlabel('Time [sec]')
plt.ylabel('Frequency [Hz]')
plt.colorbar()
plt.show()

Filters¶

In [7]:
# Filter 1
# 1000 to 1500Hz
minf, maxf = 1000, 1500

tmp_length = len(freqsSecs)//2

negative_weights = np.ones(tmp_length)
negative_weights[(freqsSecs[0:tmp_length]<-maxf)] = 0
negative_weights[(freqsSecs[0:tmp_length]>-minf)] = 0

positive_weights = np.ones(tmp_length)
positive_weights[(freqsSecs[tmp_length:]>maxf)] = 0
positive_weights[(freqsSecs[tmp_length:]<minf)] = 0

weights_1 = np.append(negative_weights,positive_weights)

plt.plot(freqsSecs, weights_1)
sns.despine()

Spectrograms for each filtered animal:¶

In [13]:
def spectrogram_plot(reconstructed_signal,sample_rate,title):
    f, t, Sxx = signal.spectrogram(reconstructed_signal, sample_rate)
    plt.pcolormesh(t, f, np.log(Sxx))
    plt.ylabel('Frequency [Hz]')
    plt.xlabel('Time [sec]')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.show()

# Animal 1
spectrogram_plot(signalFFT1_reconstructed,sample_rate,title='Animal 1')

# Animal 2
spectrogram_plot(signalFFT2_reconstructed,sample_rate,title='Animal 2')

# Animal 3
spectrogram_plot(signalFFT3_reconstructed,sample_rate,title='Animal 3')
  • Applying a smooth (Gaussian) filter for animal 2 above to see if sound quality for the animal's noise can be improved by smoother transitions between areas of the spectrum to be retained or removed.
In [14]:
# Please implement

# Smooth (Gaussian) filter for animal 2 above

minf = 3000
maxf = 4000

mu = minf + (maxf-minf)/2
sigma = (maxf-minf)/2

tmp_length = len(freqsSecs)//2

negative_smooth_weights = np.exp(-((freqsSecs[0:tmp_length]-(-mu))**2)/(2*sigma**2))
positive_smooth_weights = np.exp(-((freqsSecs[tmp_length:]-mu)**2)/(2*sigma**2))
smooth_weights = np.append(negative_smooth_weights,positive_smooth_weights)

plt.plot(freqsSecs, smooth_weights)
plt.title("Smoothed Filter")
sns.despine()

signalFFT_reconstructed = signalFFT_reconstructed.real

ipd.Audio(signalFFT_reconstructed, rate = sample_rate )
# Sounds like a bird
